EKITI  – The price of satchet water (better known as pure water) may be in­creased anytime from now as the As­sociation of Table Water Producers in Ekiti has disclosed its plan to hike the price . The zonal chairman, Oye/ Ikole, Hon.Tale Oguntoyinbo , in a state­ment made available to Daily Indepen­dent on Sunday hinted that the price of a bag of water has been increased from N150, to N200 per bag with im­mediate effect. He explained that the current eco­nomic realities cannot allow the asso­ciation to stick to the old price . OPWS Distributes Materials To IDPs In Benue, Nasarawa Edo Ranks Low In Drug Peddling, Abuse – NDLEA Official According to the release issued af­ter their meeting in Oye Ekiti, Ogun­toyinbo said for producers to be able to bring quality water to the doorsteps of consumers with the current cost of materials for water production the price cannot be less than N200 per bag. The chairman who said water is important to everybody, and water is life, added that the cost of mainte­nance, and purchase of water materi­als are going up every day. Oguntoyinbo who argued that the government had done nothing to ease the problems or assist water produc­ers in alleviating the problem.